message.content:
Rule Learning, Theory. 

Rule Learning is present in the text as the paper discusses the discovery of partial determinations, which can be seen as rules that describe dependencies between attributes in a relation. 

Theory is also present in the text as the paper proposes modifications to a known MDL formula for evaluating partial determinations and describes an efficient preprocessing-based approach for handling numerical attributes. These modifications and approaches are based on theoretical considerations and aim to improve the performance of the algorithm.
